metadata.name: Tetragons #232
metadata.description:
It all starts with a simple dot. If we enlarge it, we realize that it is in fact a square, and that we can assemble several of them, evenly spaced, to build a grid. This grid can be used as a basis for stacking a more or less large set of tetragons, and they combine with each other to form polygons, enhanced by a minimalist palette of colors, inspired by the work of Mondrian. The key to this orderly world is the use of the right angle.

Thus, everything has its place, and a place exists for everything.

---

You can download various versions of this artwork :

- press "p" to download a PNG at the current resolution of your browser
- press "h" to download a high-resolution PNG (8K) suitable for print
- press "s" to download an SVG version that you can then use to generate any image size

---

Coded with care, and with the help of p5.js, p5.js-svg and polybooljs libraries.
Consider any bug that you could get in your edition as a blessing from the RNG Gods !

metadata.name: Complex World #14
metadata.description:
"Complex World" is a genesis collection on fx(hash).
In this collection, I present to you a series of generative voxel art consisting of 36 unique pieces. These artworks are created using JSplacement, a powerful tool that generates pseudo-random 8K displacement maps.
The surfaces produced by JSplacement form the basis of these generative voxel art pieces.
The random details and vibrant colors come together to create a captivating 3D space that invites you to imagine the possibilities of a connected future,
where technology and creativity intertwine to shape new realities.

metadata.name: Tangled #37
metadata.description:
"Tangled" is a generative art project that explores the emergent behaviour of simple shapes moving according to a random flow field. While the final result is always constrained to the shape of a circle, the variation within is endless.

Instructions:
Press "p" to pause the animation.
In live mode, press 1 through 5 to save a PNG version of the final result. The following resolutions are available:
1: 400 x 400 (ideal for Twitter PFP)
2: 1000 x 1000
3: 2000 x 2000
4: 4000 x 4000
5: 5000 x 5000
Please be patient, generating the PNG may take some time!

Made with p5.js.

metadata.name: Fragmented triacontahedron with iPhone 5s #68
metadata.description:
Title: Fragmented rhombic triacontahedron with model iPhone 5s
Media: Interactive WebGL, resolution variable

A randomized composition of digital artifacts. Scans of a plaster sculpture that has been deliberately shattered. A deconstructed 3d model of an iPhone 5s. Original photography, textures, screen captures and found images. Stream of consciousness text.

* Mouse to orbit. Scroll wheel to zoom.
